metadata.name: Beacon #100
metadata.description:
Thousands of glowing beams, each with its own gradient and disappearing to a path of vanishing points. While the inspiration was figurative, drawn from the Northern Lights, the results have been taken to the abstract. Bold shapes in the foreground draw focus and their simple geometries are elevated to a signal. 

This project was created during a Speed Run over ~24 hours.
Uses WEBGL and may load a little slowly on some machines.

metadata.name: Gravity's End #40
metadata.description:
Gravity's End depicts fictional worlds being warped, distorted, and in rare cases, shattered, due to extreme gravitational forces.

Gravity's End is written with shaders, so a gpu is recommended. It is very gpu friendly, in that only one frame is rendered.

Rarities

- 21 palettes with 5 rare palettes (4% chance for rare).
- 10% chance of getting a shattered world.

Keys: 

's' saves a png in the exact size of the screen.

metadata.name: Enfold #8
metadata.description:
‚ÄúWe saw the first blossoms late that year, an anticipated promise from the tenacious, etiolated fingers we'd observed making their way through the unseasonable snow; a dirty snow. They represented hope, pushing through this gritty crust formed of equal parts ice and ash making an inevitable descent from the troposphere. We kidded ourselves it was the earth washing itself clean, erasing all evidence of what we'd done, though we knew in our secret hearts that no amount of rainfall, ironically, could save us from the flood.‚Äù

Enfold is a piece based around distance: distance from circles, distance from centres, distance from edges. Points, places and relationships between separate entities are combined and forced through curated palettes of bright and vivid colours, producing overlapping, elliptical and lens-shaped areas formed from emergent, convex arcs.

metadata.name: This is Not an Image #76
metadata.description:
When you see a piece of generative art, you are looking at a meta-message, an image whose value is not of form but of subtext. These images are a collision and reformation of ideas and conceptual histories between artists Nudoru and Sub Net. This dichotomy reminds us of the painting "The Treachery of Images" by Ren√© Magritte, where he paints a picture of a pipe but states underneath, "ceci n'est pas une pipe" (This is not a pipe), meaning that there is a schism between what a thing is and what it represents. What is unique about these works go beyond the images and text combinations themselves. It is about how images create new thoughts not by not pretending to be completely novel but that builds upon one another in a system of complex synthesis.

This token is part of the Floor Exhibit co-curated by the NFT Museum of Newberry, SC and Fort Gallery NFT.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press' p' to pause/resume.
Press' s' to save a screenshot. The image size is 2357‚Ää√ó‚Ää3000px.
